      <c01 level="series" id="d1e193">
        <did>
          <unittitle>Letters</unittitle>
        </did>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e197">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>J. S. Clark</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1867 May 27</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Mentions "Revival Literature," "Dictionary of the
                  Bible," by Smith and Harper's "Bible
                  Cyclopaedia."]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e219">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to
                  unknown</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1878 Apr 16</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Confirms the receipt of $10 for one copy of the
                  reproduction of Turner's etchings; reports on 
                  <persname>John Ruskin</persname>'s health.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e242">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>Luigi Palma di
                  Cesnola</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1883 Feb 11</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>4 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Refers to "drawings" which should be shown at the
                  conveniece of General di Cesnola; suggests Professor
                  Ware's assistance; mentions Mr. Dodge.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e264">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>James R. Osgood</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1884 Apr 7</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>3 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Suggests the printing of 2000 copies of 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Reminiscences</bibref>to be published in the 
                  <geogname>United States</geogname>; opposes a
                  publication in 
                  <geogname>England</geogname>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e295">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>Henry (?) Phillips,
                  Jr.</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1885 Sep 21</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Thanks him for a small volume of "Volk Songs"
                  which (?) Phillips has translated into English.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e317">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>James Bradstreet
                  Greenough</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1886 May 10</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>4 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Asks him to serve as chairman of a Committee on
                  Membership of the 
                  <corpname>Archaeological Institute of
                  America</corpname>; suggests 
                  <persname>Thomas Wentworth Higginson</persname>and 
                  <persname>Cardiner M. Lane</persname>as the two other
                  members.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e348">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>Bliss Carman</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1891 Aug 16</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>3 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[States that he does not intend, now or later, to
                  write about 
                  <persname>James Russell Lowell</persname>for any
                  journal of public print; suggests that people who
                  have been less close to Lowell should write about
                  him; compliments Carman on his poems.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e373">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to 
                  <persname>Francis Henry
                  Underwood</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1892 Jan 20</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>4 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Discusses a paper on 
                  <persname>James Russell Lowell</persname>by Underwood
                  which appeared in the 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Contemporary</bibref>; says he would like to
                  read Underwood's "Reminiscences" [ 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Quabbin, The Story of A Small Town</bibref>];
                  tells of his plan to publish a selection of Lowell's
                  letters with his own "slender narrative" to serve as
                  a biography; mentions poem, " 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Carter's Goat</bibref>. "]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e407">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to Mrs. 
                  <persname>Francis James
                  Lippitt</persname></unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1894 Jan 12</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>4 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Thanks her for the loan of a [Lowell] letter;
                  refers to a notice in the 
                  <bibref xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="">Nation</bibref>dealing with Lowell's
                  love-letters, claiming that they have been handed
                  about a large circle of friends; hopes that she can
                  shed light on the matter and is sure that Lowell
                  himself burned the letters, not 
                  <persname>[Mabel Lowell] Burnett</persname>. ]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
        <c02 level="item" id="d1e435">
          <did>
            <unittitle><persname>Charles Eliot Norton</persname>to Mr.
                  Kimball</unittitle>
            <unitdate era="ce" calendar="gregorian">1894 Jan 17</unitdate>
            <physdesc>
              <genreform>ALS,</genreform>
              <extent>2 p.</extent>
            </physdesc>
          </did>
          <scopecontent>
            <p>[Asks him to visit at a later date unless he has
                  to have his question answered at once.]</p>
          </scopecontent>
        </c02>
      </c01>
    </dsc>
